      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Loratadine, marketed as an antiallergy medication under the brand name Claritin, has four rings, eight double bonds, and the formula C<sub>22</sub>H<sub><span class=\"magenta-text\">?</span></sub>ClN<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>. How many hydrogens does loratadine have? (Calculate your answer; don’t count hydrogens in the structure.)</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdFlSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--49b8ee6261819fbf609ec901e26bea0f9e0ef4fb/OChem_07_EC_014.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of Loratadine.\">",
